        public void addEvent(java.lang.String name,

                     java.lang.String teacher,
                     java.lang.String faculty,
                     int attendants,
                     java.lang.String auditoriumsToReservate)
        This method receives the attributes of an event in order to create a new event and add it to its respectives auditoriums. pre: An arrayList to store all the events has already been created. post: A new event has been created and added to its correspondent container.
        Parameters:
        name - String that corresponds to the name of the event.
        date - LocalDate that corresponds to the date of the event.
        start_hour - LocalTime that corresponds to the star hour of the event.
        end_hour - LocalTime that corresponds to the end hour of the event.
        teacher - String that corresponds to the teacher in charge of the event.
        faculty - String that corresponds to the faculty that organizes the event.
        attendants - int that corresponds to the attendants time of the event.
        auditoriumsToReservate - String that correspond to the auditoriums ro reservate for the event.
